description: "The letters ‘E’ or ‘D’ are marked after place names to indicate if they are English or Dutch colonial possessions: e.g. ‘Marleborough Fort E’ on Sumatra or ‘Concordia Fort D’ on Timor. The Philippines are labelled ‘to Spain’."
title: "The principal islands of the East-Indies : explaining what belongs to England, Spain and Holland &c / by H. Moll geographer."
